cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a new method for embedding discrete structures, specifically in the context of language modeling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a new optimization technique based on stochastic gradient descent, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the proposed method can improve efficiency and mitigate overfitting, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's experiments involve language modeling, which could also suggest a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision) given the importance of natural language processing in image captioning and other vision-related tasks.
